;"></p><p>JOB POSTING # 790787</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**POSITION:** Analyst III, Financial</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**DEPARTMENT:** CBARR</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**LOCATION:** Toronto General Hospital</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**REPORTING TO:** Manager</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**STATUS:** Permanent, Full Time</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>As an integral member of the Corporate Billing, Accounts Receivable and Registration team the Analyst III plays a key role in supporting the management of accounts receivables, maximizing cash flow and revenue, implementing process improvements and revenue-generating initiatives. Leading a small team, the Analyst III monitors collection of non-patient accounts, provides a range of analysis, financial reports and metrics on the AR and revenues to support management decision making, and supports the Billing and Receivable system (HRCM) to ensure system integrity.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Responsibilities include:**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Maximizing Revenue &amp; Cash Flow**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Supervise non-patient account billing and collection activities, including Foundation, Other Hospital, Physician and other third party AR</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Prepare Balance Sheet and Income Statement budgets, forecasts and variance analysis, with recommendations on actions to improve revenue and cash flow</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Prepare and monitor AR key metrics; analyze issues and trends</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Identify, analyze and recommend improvements in revenue &amp; collections strategies and processes</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Provide analysis, problem solving and support on operational billing and collection issues, liaising with staff, hospital departments, physicians and clients.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Financial Accounting&amp;Reporting**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Prepare, analyze, and review monthly financial reports, metrics, and ad hoc analytics</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Prepare and review analysis and reconciliations on AR balance sheet accounts ranging in complexity and maintains accounts.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Prepare Provincial Consolidation schedules relating to AR for reporting to the MOHLTC</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Lead the AR team in year- end audit preparation and requirements</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Prepare bad debt analysis and provision estimate</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Provide support to management in reporting requirements as required</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Provide work direction and technical training and guidance to staff.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Ensuring integrity of HRCM System**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Ensure processes and internal controls are in place to maintain integrity of the billing system</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Oversee system maintenance, provide trouble shooting expertise</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Lead systems upgrades and troubleshooting on HRCM in partnership with Finance Systems.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Education, Training and Core competencies required</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Completion of a professional accounting program CPA Required</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Bachelorâs degree in Accounting, Finance or equivalent</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ 4 years of related experience in accounting and finance environment, preferably in hospital or health care environment</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Strong analytical and problem solving skills</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Experienced in report design, development and managing large databases.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Strong system experience including system implementation, system controls and recommends system enhancements or changes</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Advanced working knowledge of Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, Access, Power Point) required, Crystal preferred.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Experience with Infor Healthcare Revenue Cycle Management (HRCM) &amp; SAP - preferred</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Demonstrated experience supervising &amp; leading small teams</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Demonstrated commitment to client service and satisfaction</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>If you are interested in making your contribution at UHN, please apply on-line. You will be asked to copy and paste as well as attach your resume and covering letter. You will also be required to complete some initial screening questions.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**POSTED DATE:** October 3, 2016 CLOSING DATE: Until Filled</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Posting # 790787</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>For current UHN employees, only those who have successfully completed their probationary period, have a good employee record along with satisfactory attendance in accordance with UHN&#39;s attendance management program, and possess all the required experience and qualifications should apply.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>University Health Network thanks all applicants, however, only those selected for an interview will be contacted.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>UHN is a respectful, caring, and inclusive workplace. We are committed to championing accessibility, diversity and equal opportunity. Requests for accommodation can be made at any stage of the recruitment process providing the applicant has met the Bona-fide requirements for the open position. Applicants need to make their requirements known when contacted.</p><br /><br /><div style="text-align:left;padding-bottom: 20px;"><a href="/frca-apply/bjsm4b" id="ApplyBottomLink" target="_blank" class="bigBlueButtonLink" rel="nofollow" onclick="javascript:setTimeout(&quot;window.location.href = &#39;/post-resume?jid=bjsm4b&#39;;&quot;,1500); return true;">Go to apply&nbsp;<img src="/Images/apply